         Actually the earing is worth quite a bit if you are in the right position to spend PP. What else is thier to buy? I look at this way. First you are supporting Tadeskill people or you are skilling up your own skills in the quest..your choice. Then lets look at the earing itself. I could be mistaken and point me in a different direction if you can. Thier isnt any drop earing even remotely close to the stats on this earing. For a necro in the high end game..+5 stam 55hp 55 mana is huge to put into the ear slot not to mention ft1 in the ear is great as well. I paid 10k and tons of running around for the item and it was the best 10k spent and all people involved were happy. The original earing that you get from putting the 9 items into a forage and hitting combine produces a kick ass druid earing. If you have a 51 or higher druid that earing is a nice item!</P><P>Ibudin</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
