        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Buying the nine items from players will run you from 10k to 15k, depending on what sort of deals you get.</P><P>Actually skilling up multiple tradeskills to 250 is going to cost at least ten times that.  Or more.  Not to mention the time of gathering the components and doing the combines.  I saw a post on eqtraders stating that to complete one of the tougher items, it took 933 clicks.  For one attempt.</P><P>It's a great item.  Nice stats, not to mention the FT.  But it's not worth skilling up for.</P><P>On the other hand, FT1 is only what, 10 mana a minute?  That works out to 600 mana in an entire hour.  Pretty insignificant in the long term.  You'd save far, far more mana by using an item with a mana reduction focus effect, if you had to choose between earrings.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
