         You're in the wrong frame of thought when thinking of how to price this.  In order to price something you don't think, 'Well my BP has 50 more hps then this' or 'Hmm, my [insert item other then ear slot item] has more [insert stat you like] then this ear slot', because that's not how it works.  You are paying for the people who worked their ass off to get to 250 or close to 250 at what they do, which costs hundreds of thousands of pp in most cases.  You are paying for the difficulty of the combine.  You are paying for how high the earring is ranked amongst all earrings.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
